cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper is about domain adaptation for neural machine translation, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a new framework for domain adaptation that involves modeling the difference between domains, which could be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), and neural networks (cs.NE).
